# Internationalize UI strings

Never hardcode user-facing copy (labels, placeholders, button text, empty states, toast titles, aria-labels, etc.). Always use `react-intl`.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<EuiFieldSearch placeholder="Escaneie o tombo ou busque por título/autor" />

// ✅ GOOD — FormattedMessage for JSX text
<FormattedMessage
  defaultMessage="Tombo, título ou autor"
  id="circulation.return.search.label"
/>

// ✅ GOOD — useIntl when a string prop or non-JSX value is required
const { formatMessage } = useIntl()
<EuiFieldSearch
  placeholder={formatMessage({
    defaultMessage: 'Escaneie o tombo ou busque por título/autor',
    id: 'circulation.return.search.placeholder',
  })}
/>
```

- Prefer `FormattedMessage` for visible JSX children.
- Use `useIntl` / `formatMessage` for props, toast titles, and other non-JSX strings — including inside hooks.
- Give every message a stable `id` and a Portuguese `defaultMessage`.
- Do not skip i18n for "temporary" or Portuguese-only UI.
